lm_model <- 
  linear_reg() %>% 
  fit(Survived_prev ~ Sex, data = datos_o)
tidy(lm_model)
glance(lm_model)

datos_o %>% 
  group_by(Sex) %>% 
  summarise(porc_survived = sum(Survived_prev)/n())
var_p <- "Pclass"
grid.arrange(
  plot_general(var_p),
  plot_general_norm(var_p), ncol = 2
)


lm_model <- 
  linear_reg() %>% 
  fit(Survived_prev  ~ factor(Pclass), data = datos_o)

tidy(lm_model)
glance(lm_model)

datos_o %>% 
  group_by(Pclass) %>% 
  summarise(porc_survived = sum(Survived_prev)/n())
var_p <- "Age"
plot_general(var_p)

plot_general_norm(var_p)

lm_model <- 
  linear_reg() %>% 
  fit(Survived_prev  ~ Age, data = datos_o)

tidy(lm_model)
glance(lm_model)

datos_o %>% 
  group_by(Age) %>% 
  summarise(porc_survived = sum(Survived_prev)/n())
var_p <- "Title"
plot_general(var_p)

plot_general_norm(var_p)

lm_model <- 
  linear_reg() %>% 
  fit(Survived_prev  ~ Title, data = datos_o)

tidy(lm_model)
glance(lm_model)

datos_o %>% 
  group_by(Title) %>% 
  summarise(porc_survived = sum(Survived_prev)/n())
lm_model <- 
  linear_reg() %>% 
  fit(Survived_prev  ~ Sex+factor(Pclass)+Age, data = datos_o)

tidy(lm_model)
glance(lm_model)

datos_o %>% 
  group_by(Sex, Pclass, Age) %>% 
  summarise(porc_survived = sum(Survived_prev)/n()) %>% 
  arrange(desc(porc_survived)) %>% data.frame() %>% 
  filter(Sex == "male", Pclass == 2, Age == "[45-65) \n Adultos Maduros")
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'Sex', 'Pclass'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
